circus world ( released as the magnificent &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; in the united kingdom ) is a 1964 drama film starring john wayne , claudia cardinale and rita hayworth . it was directed by henry hathaway and produced by samuel bronston , with a screenplay by ben hecht , julian &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; and james edward grant , from a story by bernard gordon and nicholas ray . the film won the golden globe award for best song for dimitri tiomkin and ned washington ( lyrics ) , while rita hayworth was nominated for the best actress award .